<subSubSection id="51DA6520FF97FFF6A3E3BFFBFAB9F6DB" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="197F36ABFF97FFF6A3E3BFFBFAB9F6DB" blockId="9.[136,1452,1153,1252]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">
The species grows on vulcanic rocks and it is classified as critically endangered (CR) in its native habitat (IUCN 2022). The populations found are small and disjunct in an area of about 
<quantity id="DE389B4EFF97FFF6A00DBFDFFC78F680" box="[870,941,1189,1215]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="km" value="14.0">14 km</quantity>
<superScript id="EEB59BE3FF97FFF6A0C6BFDFFC60F68C" attach="left" box="[941,949,1189,1203]" fontSize="6" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">2</superScript>
. The threats observed were human activities associated with agriculture (removal of soil cover and removal of stones from the field) and livestock (grazing).
</paragraph>
